        "text": "2 Chronicles 34:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); and the sun-pillars (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 14:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") which stood upwards, i.e., above, upon the altars, he caused to be hewn away from them (מעליהם); the Asherim (pillars and trees of Asherah) and the carved and molten images to be broken and ground (הדק, cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 15:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and (the dust of them) to be strewn upon the graves (of those) who had sacrificed to them. הזּבחים is connected directly with הקּברים, so that the actions of those buried in them are poetically attributed to the graves. In ",
